{
  "stem": "12289.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, the next experience I had was I had heard that outside, just outside Budapest, they had, in a-- in a factory, on the compound of a factory there, collected thousands of Jewish people, who were standing or sitting like under-- in the open air, a whole week without food or anything.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were in a miserable condition, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I said, well, why don't I try to see how that is?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I went there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I found then the whole place fenced in, like that, around the factory buildings.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on the-- on the place there, there were all these Jews lying there or standing or-- or-- or waiting for something.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that something was a train coming in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- the door were opened-- was opened.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the people were pushed into these cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I saw how one soldier took a small boy, by his leg, and threw him in like that, into the car, you know?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and when they have packed that car completely, they put in a bucket of water just to show how-- this humanitarian gesture.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they closed-- they nailed the-- the doors.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then that train, as I heard afterwards, was circulating a whole week in-- in Buda-- in Hungary till they were transferred over to Auschwitz, when the-- a big part of these-- of the Jewish people were-- were dead or got insane or, you know, all that.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was the most-- most barbaric, most terrible way of-- of deporting people, as I thought then.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would have experience of another, which was, perhaps, the same cruel method but in another way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was when I was with Raoul Wallenberg, now and then, at these so-called death marches from Budapest to-- to Hegyeshalom.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
